{'GreenhouseDT': {'description': 'The **GreenhouseDT** does **not explicitly adhere to any industry standards**. The system uses **InfluxDB** (open-source time-series database) and **ActiveMQ** (open-source message broker) without reference to formal specifications. Deployment relies on **virtual machine images** and **GitHub**, which are non-standardized governance tools. No certification or interoperability frameworks are mentioned.'}, 'Air Quality Management': {'description': 'The **Air Quality Management** Digital Twin **implicitly references AutomationML** (a standardized modeling language for industrial systems) but does **not explicitly cite ISO 15926-11 or other formal standards**. The system leverages **Microsoft Azure** for pipeline implementation, which may align with Microsoft\u2019s enterprise standards, but no explicit compliance is stated. Interoperability is achieved via **AutomationML-based twin modeling** and **Raspberry Pi sensor integration**, though no broader standardization framework (e.g., IEC 62424) is mentioned.'}, 'Lab Scale Gantry Crane': {'description': 'The **Lab Scale Gantry Crane** does **not explicitly adhere to any standardization frameworks**. The twinning process uses **DarTwin notation** (a custom approach) and **Docker containers** for deployment, with no reference to industry standards (e.g., IEC 62424). Governance is ad-hoc, relying on **GitHub** and **C4 Model diagrams** for architectural documentation. No certification or interoperability requirements are mentioned.'}}